pageContext.claim: “And we are coming back as a country like nobody has ever seen. When I'm greeted -- and I'm often greeted -- by leaders of the world, they start off by saying two things: 'Congratulations on what you've done with your country, from an economic standpoint. We've never seen anything like it.' And, 'Sir, congratulations on rebuilding your military.' And that's what we've done.”
pageContext.analysis: Foreign leaders have not said this publicly, and there’s no evidence they’ve said it in private.
